  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary aim of this study is to evaluate if multiple postoperative administrations with a
      solution of ropivacaine, ketorolac and epinephrine into the operating field through a
      catheter would affect morphine consumption. Secondary end-points are pain intensity, side
      effects and length of stay.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
